17. The trimeric polypeptide complex according to claim 1, wherein the at least one heterologous moiety is selected from the group consisting of:
(a) a ligand binding structure;
(b) a toxin;
(c) a detectable moiety;
(d) an in situ activatable substance;
(e) an enzyme;
(f) a radioactive moiety;
(g) a cytokine;
(h) a non-proteinaceous polymer;
(i) a polyalcohol;
(j) a polysaccharide;
(k) a lipid;
(l) a polyamine;
(m) a photo cross-linking agent; and
(n) a group facilitating conjugation of the polypeptide to a target, wherein the conjugation encompasses both covalent and non-covalent linkages.

